    String C350113LimitGrowth_B = "(B) Completely submerged under running water:\n" +
            "(1) At a water temperature of 21°C (70°F) or below,\n" +
            "(2) With sufficient water velocity to agitate and float off loose particles in an overflow, and\n" +
            "(3) For a period of time that does not allow thawed portions of READY-TO-EAT FOOD to rise above 5°C (41°F), or\n" +
            "(4) For a period of time that does not allow thawed portions of a raw animal\n" +
            "FOOD requiring cooking as specified under 3-401.11(A) or (B) to be above\n" +
            "5°C (41°F), for more than 4 hours including:\n" +
            "(a) The time the FOOD is exposed to the running water and the time needed for preparation for cooking, or\n" +
            "(b) The time it takes under refrigeration to lower the FOOD temperature to 5°C (41°F).";
    String C350113LimitGrowth_C = "(C) As part of a cooking process if the FOOD that is frozen is:\n" +
            "(1) Cooked as specified under Subparagraphs 3-401.11(A) or (B) or Subpart\n" +
            "3-401.12, or\n" +
            "(2) Thawed in a microwave oven and immediately transferred to conventional cooking EQUIPMENT, with no interruption in the process;";
    String C350113LimitGrowth_D = "(D) Using any procedure if a portion of frozen READY-TO-EAT FOOD is thawed and prepared for immediate service in response to an individual CONSUMER'S order.";


    String C350114LimitGrowth_A = "(A) Cooked POTENTIALLY HAZARDOUS FOOD (Time/Temperature Control for Safety\n" +
            "Food) shall be cooled:\n" +
            "(1) Within 2 hours from 57°C (135°F) to 21°C (70°F); P and\n" +
            "(2) Within 6 hours from 57°C (135°F) to 5°C (41°F) or less. P";
    String C350114LimitGrowth_B = "(B) POTENTIALLY HAZARDOUS FOOD (Time/Temperature Control for Safety Food) shall be cooled within 4 hours to 5°C (41°F) or less, if prepared from ingredients at ambient temperature, such as reconstituted FOODS and canned tuna. P";
    String C350114LimitGrowth_C = "(C) Except as specified in Subparagraph (D) of this section, a POTENTIALLY HAZARDOUS FOOD (Time/Temperature Control for Safety Food) received in compliance with LAWS allowing a temperature above 5°C (41°F) during shipment\n" +
            "o\n" +
            "from the supplier as specified in 3202.11(B), shall be cooled within 4 hours to 5 C\n" +
            "(41 F) or less. P";
    String C350114LimitGrowth_D = "(D) Raw EGGS shall be received as specified under Subparagraph 3-202.11(C) and immediately placed in refrigerated equipment that maintains an ambient air temperature of 7°C (45°F) or less. P";



    String C350115LimitGrowth_A = "(A) Cooling shall be accomplished in accordance with the time and temperature criteria specified under Subpart 3-501.14 by using one or more of the following methods based on the type of FOOD being cooled:\n" +
            "(1) Placing the FOOD in shallow pans; Pf\n" +
            "(2) Separating the FOOD into smaller or thinner portions; Pf\n" +
            "(3) Using rapid cooling EQUIPMENT; Pf\n" +
            "(4) Stirring the FOOD in a container placed in an ice water bath; Pf\n" +
            "(5) Using containers that facilitate heat transfer; Pf\n" +
            "(6) Adding ice as an ingredient; Pf or\n" +
            "(7) Other effective methods. Pf";
    String C350115LimitGrowth_B = "(B) When placed in cooling or cold holding EQUIPMENT, FOOD containers in which\n" +
            "FOOD is being cooled shall be:\n" +
            "(1) Arranged in the EQUIPMENT to provide maximum heat transfer through the container walls; and\n" +
            "(2) Loosely covered, or uncovered if protected from overhead contamination\n" +
            "as specified under Subparagraph 3-305.11(A)(2), during the cooling period to facilitate heat transfer from the surface of the FOOD";

    String C350116LimitGrowth_A = "(A) Except during preparation, cooking, or cooling, or when time is used as the public health control as specified in Subpart 3-501.19, and except as specified in Subparagraph (B) of this section, POTENTIALLY HAZARDOUS FOOD (Time/Temperature Control for Safety Food) shall be maintained:\n" +
            "(1) At 57°C (135°F) or above, except that roasts cooked to a temperature and for a time specified in Subparagraph 3-401.11(B) or reheated as specified\n" +
            "o o\n" +
            "in Subparagraph 3-403.11(E) may be held at a temperature of 54 C (130 F)\n" +
            "or above; P or\n" +
            "(2) At 5°C (41°F) or less. P";
    String C350116LimitGrowth_B = "(B) EGGS that have not been treated to destroy all viable Salmonellae spp. shall be stored in refrigerated EQUIPMENT that maintains an ambient air temperature of 7°C (45°F) or less. P";
    String C350116LimitGrowth_C = "(C) POTENTIALLY HAZARDOUS FOOD (TIME/TEMPERATURE CONTROL FOR SAFETY FOOD) in a homogenous liquid form may be maintained outside of the temperature control requirements, as specified under (A) of this section, while contained within specially designed EQUIPMENT that complies with the design and construction requirements as specified under 4-204.13(E).";


    String C350117LimitGrowth_A = "(A) Except when PACKAGING FOOD using a REDUCED OXYGEN PACKAGING method as specified under paragraph 3-502.12, and except as specified in (D) and (E) of this section, refrigerated, READY-TO-EAT, POTENTIALLY HAZARDOUS FOOD (TIME/TEMPERATURE CONTROL FOR SAFETY FOOD) prepared and held in a FOOD ESTABLISHMENT for more than 24 hours shall be clearly marked to indicate the date or day by which the FOOD shall be consumed on the PREMISES, sold, or discarded when held at a temperature of 5ºC (41ºF) or less for a maximum of 7 days. Pf";
    String C350117LimitGrowth_B = "(B) Except as specified in Paragraphs (D) and (E) of this section, refrigerated, READY- TO-EAT, POTENTIALLY HAZARDOUS FOOD (Time/Temperature Control for Safety\n" +
            "Food) prepared and PACKAGED by a FOOD PROCESSING PLANT shall be clearly marked, at the time the original container is opened in a FOOD ESTABLISHMENT and if the FOOD is held for more than 24 hours, to indicate the date or day by which\n" +
            "the FOOD shall be consumed on the PREMISES, sold, or discarded, based on the temperature specified in (A) of this section; and: Pf\n" +
            "(1) The day the original container is opened in the RETAIL FOOD ESTABLISHMENT\n" +
            "shall be counted as Day 1; Pf and\n" +
            "(2) The day or date marked by the RETAIL FOOD ESTABLISHMENT may not exceed a manufacturer’s use-by date if the manufacturer determined the use-by date based on FOOD safety. Pf";
    String C350117LimitGrowth_C = "(C) A refrigerated, READY-TO-EAT POTENTIALLY HAZARDOUS FOOD (Time/Temperature Control for Safety Food ingredient or a portion of a refrigerated, READY-TO-EAT, POTENTIALLY HAZARDOUS FOOD (TIME/TEMPERATURE CONTROL FOR SAFETY FOOD) that is subsequently combined with additional ingredients or portions of FOOD shall retain the date marking of the earliest-prepared or first-prepared ingredient. Pf";
    String C350117LimitGrowth_D = "(D) A date marking system that meets the criteria stated in (A) and (B) of this section may include:\n" +
            "(1) Using a method APPROVED by the REGULATORY AUTHORITY for refrigerated, READY-TO-EAT POTENTIALLY HAZARDOUS FOOD (TIME/TEMPERATURE CONTROL FOR SAFETY FOOD) that is frequently rewrapped, such as lunchmeat or a roast, or for which date marking is impractical, such as soft serve mix or milk in a dispensing machine;\n" +
            "(2) Marking the date or day of preparation, with a procedure to discard the FOOD on or before the last date or day by which the FOOD must be consumed on the premises, sold, or discarded as specified under (A) of this section;\n" +
            "(3) Marking the date or day the original container is opened in a FOOD ESTABLISHMENT, with a procedure to discard the FOOD on or before the last date or day by which the FOOD must be consumed on the premises, sold, or discarded as specified under (B) of this section; or" +
            "(4) Using calendar dates, days of the week, color-coded marks, or other effective marking methods, provided that the marking system is disclosed to the REGULATORY AUTHORITY upon request.";
    String C350117LimitGrowth_E = "(E) Paragraphs (A) and (B) of this section do not apply to individual meal portions served or rePACKAGED for sale from a bulk container upon a consumer's request.";
    String C350117LimitGrowth_F = "(F) Paragraph (B) of this section does not apply to the following FOODS prepared and\n" +
            "PACKAGED by a FOOD PROCESSING PLANT inspected by a REGULATORY AUTHORITY:\n" +
            "(1) Deli salads, such as ham salad, seafood salad, chicken salad, egg salad, pasta salad, potato salad, and macaroni salad, manufactured in accordance with 21 CFR 110 Current good manufacturing practice in manufacturing, packing, or holding human food;\n" +
            "(2) Hard cheeses containing not more than 39% moisture as defined in 21\n" +
            "CFR 133 Cheeses and related cheese products, such as cheddar, gruyere, parmesan and reggiano, and romano;\n" +
            "(3) Semi-soft cheeses containing more than 39% moisture, but not more than\n" +
            "50% moisture, as defined in 21 CFR 133 Cheeses and related cheese products, such as blue, edam, gorgonzola, gouda, and monterey jack;\n" +
            "(4) Cultured dairy products as defined in 21 CFR 131 Milk and cream, such as yogurt, sour cream, and buttermilk;\n" +
            "(5) Preserved FISH products, such as pickled herring and dried or salted cod, and other acidified FISH products defined in 21 CFR 114 Acidified foods;\n" +
            "(6) Shelf stable, dry fermented sausages, such as pepperoni and Genoa salami that are not labeled \"Keep Refrigerated\" as specified in 9 CFR 317\n" +
            "Labeling, marking devices, and containers, and which retain the original\n" +
            "CASING on the product; and\n" +
            "(7) Shelf stable salt-cured products such as prosciutto and Parma (ham) that are not labeled \"Keep Refrigerated\" as specified in 9 CFR 317 Labeling, marking devices, and containers.";


    String C350118LimitGrowth_A = "(A) A FOOD specified in Subparagraphs 3-501.17(A) or (B) shall be discarded if it: (1) Exceeds either of the temperature and time combinations specified in\n" +
            "Subparagraph 3-501.17(A), except time that the product is frozen; P\n" +
            "(2) Is in a container or PACKAGE that does not bear a date or day; P or\n" +
            "(3) Is appropriately marked with a date or day that exceeds a temperature and time combination as specified in Subparagraph 3-501.17(A). P";
    String C350118LimitGrowth_B = "(B) Refrigerated, READY-TO-EAT, POTENTIALLY HAZARDOUS FOOD (Time/Temperature Control for Safety Food) prepared in a FOOD ESTABLISHMENT and dispensed through a VENDING MACHINE with an automatic shutoff control shall be discarded if it exceeds a temperature and time combination as specified in Subparagraph 3-\n" +
            "501.17(A). P";


    String C350119LimitGrowth_A = "(A) Except as specified under Paragraph (B) of this section, if time without temperature control, is used as the public health control for a working supply of POTENTIALLY HAZARDOUS FOOD (Time/Temperature Control for Safety Food) before cooking, or for READY-TO-EAT POTENTIALLY HAZARDOUS FOOD (Time/Temperature Control for Safety Food) that is displayed or held for sale or service:\n" +
            "(1) Written procedures shall be prepared in advance, maintained in the FOOD ESTABLISHMENT and made available to the REGULATORY AUTHORITY upon request that specify: Pf\n" +
            "(a) Methods of compliance with Subparagraphs (B)(1) -(3) or C)(1)-(5) of this section; Pf and\n" +
            "(b) Methods of compliance with 3-501.14 for FOOD that is prepared, cooked, and refrigerated before time is used as a public health control. Pf";
    String C350119LimitGrowth_B = "(B) If time temperature control is used as the public health control up to a maximum of 4 hours:\n" +
            "TIME- maximum up to 4 hours\n" +
            "(1) The FOOD shall have an initial temperature of 5ºC (41ºF) or less when removed from cold holding temperature control, or 57°C (135°F) or greater when removed from hot holding temperature control; P\n" +
            "(2) The FOOD shall be marked or otherwise identified to indicate the time that is\n" +
            "4 hours past the point in time when the FOOD is removed from temperature control; Pf\n" +
            "(3) The FOOD shall be cooked and served, served at any temperature if READY- TO-EAT, or discarded, within 4 hours from the point in time when the FOOD is removed from temperature control; P and\n" +
            "(4) The FOOD in unmarked containers or PACKAGES, or marked to exceed a 4- hour limit shall be discarded. P";
    String C350119LimitGrowth_C = "(C) A FOOD ESTABLISHMENT that serves a HIGHLY SUSCEPTIBLE POPULATION may not use time as specified under (A) or (B) of this section as the public health control for raw EGGS.";


    String C350211LimitGrowth_A = "A RETAIL FOOD ESTABLISHMENT shall obtain a VARIANCE from the REGULATORY AUTHORITY\n" +
            "as specified in Subpart 8-103.10 and under Subpart 8-103.11 before: Pf\n" +
            "(A) Smoking FOOD as a method of FOOD preservation rather than as a method of flavor enhancement; Pf";
    String C350211LimitGrowth_B = "(B) Curing FOOD; Pf";
    String C350211LimitGrowth_C = "(C) Using FOOD ADDITIVES or adding components such as vinegar: Pf\n" +
            "(1) As a method of FOOD preservation rather than as a method of flavor enhancement, Pf or\n" +
            "(2) To render a FOOD so that it is not POTENTIALLY HAZARDOUS; Pf";
    String C350211LimitGrowth_D = "(D) Packaging FOOD using a REDUCED OXYGEN PACKAGING method except where the growth of a toxin formation by Clostridium botulinum and the growth of Listeria monocytogenes are controlled as specified in 3-502.12; Pf";
    String C350211LimitGrowth_E = "(E) Operating a MOLLUSCAN SHELLFISH life-support system display tank used to store and display shellfish that are offered for human consumption; Pf";
    String C350211LimitGrowth_F = "(F) Custom processing animals that are for personal use as FOOD and not for sale or service in a RETAIL FOOD ESTABLISHMENT; Pf";
    String C350211LimitGrowth_G = "(G) Preparing FOOD by another method that is determined by the REGULATORY AUTHORITY to require a VARIANCE; Pf";
    String C350211LimitGrowth_H = "(H) Sprouting seeds or beans. Pf";


    String C350212LimitGrowth_A = "(A) Except for a RETAIL FOOD ESTABLISHMENT that obtains a VARIANCE as specified under 3-502.11 a FOOD ESTABLISHMENT that packages POTENTIALLY HAZARDOUS FOOD (TIME /TEMPERATURE CONTROL FOR SAFETY FOOD) using a REDUCED OXYGEN PACKAGING method shall control the growth and toxin formation of Clostridium botulinum\n" +
            "and the growth of Listeria monocytogenes. P";
    String C350212LimitGrowth_B = "(B) A FOOD ESTABLISHMENT that packages POTENTIALLY HAZARDOUS FOOD (TIME/TEMPERATURE CONTROL FOR SAFETY FOOD) using a REDUCED OXYGEN PACKAGING method shall have a HACCP PLAN that contains the information specified under 8-\n" +
            "201.14(D) and that: Pf\n" +
            "(1) Identifies the FOOD to be PACKAGED; Pf\n" +
            "(2) Except as specified under (C) - (E) of this section, requires that the PACKAGED FOOD shall be maintained at 5°C (41°F) or less and meet at least one of the following criteria: Pf\n" +
            "(a) Has an aw of 0.91 or less, (b) Has a pH of 4.6 or less, Pf\n" +
            "(c) Is a MEAT or POULTRY product cured at a FOOD PROCESSING PLANT\n" +
            "regulated by the U.S.D.A. using substances specified in 9 CFR\n" +
            "424.21, Use of food ingredients and sources of radiation, and is received in an intact package, Pf or\n" +
            "(d) Is a FOOD with a high level of competing organisms such as raw\n" +
            "MEAT, raw POULTRY or raw vegetables; Pf\n" +
            "(3) Describes how the PACKAGE shall be prominently and conspicuously labeled on the principal display panel in bold type on a contrasting background, with instructions to; Pf\n" +
            "(a) Maintain the FOOD at 5°C (41°F) or below, Pf and" +
            "(b) Discard the FOOD if within 14 calendar days of its PACKAGING it is not served for on-PREMISES consumption, or consumed if served or sold for off-PREMISES consumption; Pf\n" +
            "(4) Limits the refrigerated shelf life to no more than 14 calendar days from PACKAGING to consumption, except the time the product is maintained frozen, or the original manufacturer's \"sell by\" or \"use by\" date, whichever occurs first: P\n" +
            "(5) Includes operational procedures that:\n" +
            "(a) Prohibit contacting READY-TO-EAT FOOD with bare hands, under\n" +
            "3-301.11(B) Pf\n" +
            "(b) Identify a designated work area and the method by which: Pf\n" +
            "(i) Physical barriers or methods of separation of raw FOODS and\n" +
            "READY-TO-EAT FOODS minimize cross contamination, Pf and\n" +
            "(ii) Access to the processing EQUIPMENT is limited to responsible trained personnel familiar with the potential HAZARDS of the operation, Pf and\n" +
            "(c) Delineate cleaning and SANITIZATION procedures for FOOD-CONTACT SURFACES; Pf and\n" +
            "(6) Describes the training program that ensures that the individual responsible for the REDUCED OXYGEN PACKAGING operation understands the: Pf\n" +
            "(a) Concepts required for a safe operation, Pf\n" +
            "(b) EQUIPMENT and facilities, Pf and\n" +
            "(c) Procedures specified under Subparagraph (B)(5) of this section and\n" +
            "Subparagraph 8-201.14(D). Pf";
    String C350212LimitGrowth_C = "(C) Except for FISH that is frozen before, during, and after packaging, a FOOD ESTABLISHMENT may not package FISH using a REDUCED OXYGEN PACKAGING method P";
    String C350212LimitGrowth_D = "(D) Except as specified under (C) of this section, a FOOD ESTABLISHMENT that\n" +
            "PACKAGES FOOD using a cook-chill or sous vide process shall:\n" +
            "(1) Implement a HACCP PLAN that contains the information as specified under\n" +
            "8-201.14(D); Pf\n" +
            "(2) Ensure the FOOD is:\n" +
            "(a) Prepared and consumed on the PREMISES, or prepared and consumed off the PREMISES but within the same business entity with no distribution or sale of the PACKAGED product to another business entity or the CONSUMER, Pf\n" +
            "(b) Cooked to heat all parts of the FOOD to a temperature and for a time as specified under paragraph 3-401.11, P\n" +
            "(c) Protected from contamination before and after cooking as specified under Parts 3-3 and 3-4, P" +
            "(d) Placed in a PACKAGE with an oxygen barrier and sealed before cooking, or placed in a PACKAGE and sealed immediately after cooking and before reaching a temperature below 57°C (135°F), P\n" +
            "(e) Cooled to 5°C (41°F) in the sealed PACKAGE or bag as specified under paragraph 3-501.14 and subsequently: P\n" +
            "(i) Cooled to 1°C (34°F) within 48 hours of reaching 5°C (41°F) and held at that temperature until consumed or discarded within 30 days after the date of PACKAGING; P\n" +
            "(ii) Cooled to 1°C (34°F) within 48 hours of reaching 5°C (41°F), removed from refrigeration equipment that maintains a 1°C (34°F) food temperature and then held at 5°C (41°F) or less for no more than 72 hours, at which time the FOOD must be consumed or discarded; P\n" +
            "(iii) Cooled to 3°C (38°F) or less within 24 hours of reaching 5°C (41°F) and held there for no more than 72 hours from PACKAGING, at which time the food must be consumed or discarded; P or\n" +
            "(iv) Held frozen with no shelf life restriction while frozen until consumed or used P\n" +
            "(f) Held in a refrigeration unit that is equipped with an electronic system that continuously monitors time and temperature and is visually examined for proper operation twice daily, Pf\n" +
            "(g) If transported off-site to a satellite location of the same business entity, equipped with verifiable electronic monitoring devices to ensure that times and temperatures are monitored during transportation, Pf and\n" +
            "(h) Labeled with the product name and the date PACKAGED; Pf and\n" +
            "(3) Maintain the records required to confirm that cooling and cold holding refrigeration time/temperature parameters are required as part of the HACCP PLAN and:\n" +
            "(a) Make such records available to the REGULATORY AUTHORITY upon request, Pf and\n" +
            "(b) Hold such records for at least 6 months; Pf and\n" +
            "(4) Implement written operational procedures as specified under (B)(5) of this section and a training program as specified under (B)(6) of this section. Pf";
    String C350212LimitGrowth_E = "(E) A FOOD ESTABLISHMENT that PACKAGES cheese using a REDUCED OXYGEN PACKAGING method shall:\n" +
            "(1) Limit the cheeses PACKAGED to those that are commercially manufactured in a FOOD PROCESSING PLANT with no ingredients added in the FOOD ESTABLISHMENT and that meet the Standards of Identity as specified in 21\n" +
            "CFR 133.150 Hard cheeses, 21 CFR 133.169 Pasteurized process cheese or 21 CFR 133.187 Semisoft cheeses; P" +
            "(2) Have a HACCP PLAN that contains the information specified under 8-\n" +
            "201.14(D) and as specified under (B)(1), (B)(3)(a), (B)(5) and (B)(6) of this section; Pf\n" +
            "(3) Labels the PACKAGE on the principal display panel with a \"use by\" date that does not exceed 30 days from its packaging or the original manufacturer's \"sell by\" or \"use by\" date, whichever occurs first; Pf and\n" +
            "(4) Discards the REDUCED OXYGEN PACKAGED cheese if it is not sold for off- PREMISES consumption or consumed within 30 calendar days of its PACKAGING. Pf";


    String C360111IdentLabel = "PACKAGED FOOD shall comply with standard of identity requirements in 21 CRF 131-169 and 9 CFR 319 Definitions and Standards of Identity or Composition, and the general requirements in 21 CFR 130 – Food Standards: General and 9 CFR 319 Subpart A – General.";

